OL,3,CStorm Chandra and the growing flood
OL,4,Crisk facing the UK
OL,6,FStorm Chandra arrived at a point when
OL,7,Flarge parts of the UK were already
OL,8,Fvulnerable.
OL,10,FHuge swathes of the UK had been
OL,11,Fsaturated by weeks of persistent
OL,12,Frainfall, leaving little capacity for
OL,13,Fthe ground to absorb more water.
OL,15,FWhen Chandra brought further heavy
OL,16,Frain, rapid runoff into rivers and
OL,17,Fdrainage systems made localised
OL,18,Fflooding an inevitability.
