OL,3,CStorm Chandra and the growing flood
OL,4,Crisk facing the UK
OL,6,FIs this flooding the result of climate
OL,7,Fchange?
OL,9,FWhile Storm Chandra itself cannot be
OL,10,Fblamed solely on climate change, the
OL,11,Fconditions that made flooding more
OL,12,Flikely certainly can.
OL,14,FWithout a doubt, climate change is
OL,15,Fleading to more intense rainfall.
OL,17,FThis is because a warmer atmosphere
OL,18,Fcan hold more moisture (around 7% more
OL,19,Fwater vapour for every 1C rise in
OL,20,Ftemperature) - essentially, when it
OL,21,Frains, it rains more.
